<TEXT>
arizonas attorney general took initial 
steps friday toward investigating gov rose moffords expenditures 
of thousands of dollars in state funds on gifts and decorations 
when she was secretary of state 
some of the spending appears to have lacked legislative 
authorization according to records and interviews with officials 
although the governor and a close aide said the legislature had 
approved the funds 
mrs moffords office issued a statement saying she stands 
behind all the expenditures press aide vada manager said the 
governor would not hold a news conference on the issue because i 
dont think theres anything serious enough to have a press 
conference over 
the governor in a brief interview with radio station kfyi said 
i never misspent a penny it was appropriated for vip gifts and i 
used it for that type of purpose i never used anything for 
personal gain 
mrs mofford 65 became governor april 4 when evan mecham was 
removed from office upon being convicted in a senate impeachment 
trial of misusing state funds and obstructing justice 
records examined by the associated press showed that mrs 
moffords gift expenditures totaled at least 50000 for her last 
five years as secretary of state 
mrs mofford used state funds to pay for such things as a 
jokewriting service and diet food as well as paintings watches 
indian kachina dolls clocks flags and knickknacks typically 
charging them to other operating expenses or supplies 
house speaker joe lane said he would wait to hear from attorney 
general bob corbin and maricopa county attorney tom collins before 
deciding whether to launch an impeachment probe 
since corbin is next in line to succeed mrs mofford he already 
had turned over to collins an investigation of her financial 
disclosure practices that investigation stemmed from an ap report 
that while secretary of state she had failed to include a number of 
her business dealings in the staterequired reports 
corbin said friday that collins had agreed to investigate the 
gift expenditures as well he added that whether any criminal or 
civil action will be taken will depend on what collins finds 
mrs mofford did not respond to ap queries about the gifts and 
spoke only briefly to kfyi 
earlier this month she had said that when faced with the need 
to present gifts to important visitors as secretary of state she 
took care of it myself 
ive paid for a lot of my dinners and all those artifacts and 
things that are there mrs mofford continued only gifts we 
have a fund for vip gifts that we are permitted to use that was 
appropriated by the legislature other than that i pay for it out 
of my own pocket 
karen osborne assistant secretary of state said the 
expenditures had been authorized by the legislature as early as 
1980 when mrs mofford requested permission to spend 5000 to make 
some kind of presentation to visiting dignitaries on behalf of 
the state 
the legislatures official records show 2400 in unspecified 
other expenses was approved that year and 2500 in 1981 more 
recently the legislature has provided lumpsum allocations for the 
secretary of states office with little direction as to how the 
funds are divided the budget this year is 19 million 
laurie drobny the joint legislative budget committees staff 
analyst for the secretary of states office in 1980 said she 
didnt believe the 2400 was for gifts but that she could not 
recall what it was for 
lane also said he didnt know the money was for gifts he added 
that he could understand some of the purchases but that buying a 
joke service or diet food blows my mind 
the state constitution bars the state from giving anything of 
value to an individual without public benefit and state law makes 
unauthorized expenditures of public funds a felony 
mrs osborne said she considered that gifts mrs mofford gave as 
secretary of state did result in a public benefit because they 
were aimed at pleasing someone who could bring business to the 
state were in recognition of service to the state or were aimed at 
motivating future conduct 
records for use of state funds the past five years ago show that 
as secretary of state mrs mofford spent about 9000 on pens and 
other novelties with her name on them about 6400 on 30 watches 
bearing the state seal and about 5700 on kachina and other dolls 
and their display cases 
the total also included about 11000 for flags mostly state 
and national some of which were bought from unauthorized vendors 
at higher prices than those paid to authorized vendors for similar 
flags 
other expenditures included 20370 for a weightreduction 
product shipped to a friend and business partner of mrs mofford 
and 306 for the five years annual renewal of a joke service that 
promises to supply speakers with 120 to 140 new jokes and stories a 
month 
mrs osborne called that probably the greatest tool in the 
world since nobody wants to hear a dull totally dry speech 
as for the diet food mrs osborne said she didnt know anything 
about it 
a 1978 protocolfund statute allows the governor house speaker 
and senate president to make gifts that promote state interests and 
encourage public service it does not include the secretary of 
state 
after she became governor mrs mofford said she wanted mechams 
privately raised protocol fund money he was convicted by the 
senate of misusing placed in the state general fund that comes 
from tax revenues 
i would not have a protocol fund period she said i 
dont want one 
</TEXT>
