defending champ johnny chan capped his 
comeback fight with a queenhigh straight on the final hand 
thursday to beat rookie eric seidel of new york for the 700000 
first prize in the world series of poker 
chan who at one point was down more than 11 million in chips 
to seidel used the straight to beat seidels two queens and win 
the final 592000 pot its not over until its over said 
chan i wasnt about to give up 
it was the second straight world series win for the 30yearold 
las vegas restaurateur who beat a field of 167 players over four 
days in the texas hold em tournament 
chan who entered the final days table of six remaining players 
with 529000 in chips and the lead had only 270000 in chips to 
14 million for seidel when headtohead play among the two 
finalists began 
chan risked all his chips on the first hand against seidel who 
folded then steadily mounted a comeback that saw him go ahead with 
12 million in chips to 470000 for seidel 
seidel however came back to win the games biggest pot more 
than 12 million with a pair of 9s to chans pair of 8s and the 
game turned into a marathon with both players betting 
conservatively 
seidel 28 playing in his first series was down to 296000 
when he threw all his chips in on the pair of queens im not 
unhappy with what i did but it would have been nice to win he 
said he wins 280000 for second place 
finishing third and winning 140000 was ron graham of tacoma 
wash humberto bremnes of costa rico earned 77000 for fourth 
while tj cloutier of dallas won 63000 for fifth place 
