an explosion blew a 12ton metal door off 
a pressure vessel at general electric cos steam turbine plant 
thursday killing one worker and injuring two others 
the explosion took place at about 340 am in building 273 the 
largest building and main manufacturing plant for steam turbines 
and generators at the schenectady plant said ge spokesman larry 
stone 
killed in the explosion was 60yearold thomas dwojakowski of 
schenectady a ge worker since 1956 stone said 
stone said a metal door weighing 12 tons was blown off the 
pressure vessel called an autoclave used in curing insulation 
applied to a component in the manufacturing of generators 
the federal occupational safety and health administration is 
investigating the accident stone said as well as ges own 
investigation team 
