prime minister wilfried martens new 
government won a senate vote of confidence in a step toward 
advancing its program to end the countrys ageold linguistic 
strife 
the vote thursday endorsed the program of the 10dayold 
centerleft government that the house of representatives approved 
on sunday 
the votes came seven months after martens previous centerright 
alliance government fell apart in a linguistic dispute 
martens now plans to put into effect sweeping constitutional 
reforms to quell perennial bickering between belgiums 55 million 
dutch speakers and 45 million french speakers his new alliance 
plans to boost the powers of autonomy of northern flanders and 
southern wallonia belgiums two linguistic regions 
the prime minister has said he will send the constitutional 
changes by august to parliament where he will need a twothirds 
majority 
