needs of the east coast restaurant trade 
but the firm stopped slaughtering last year because farms in 
the region could not provide enough lambs and animals had to be 
shipped in from the west stillman said 
predators including coyotes and wild or roaming dogs also have 
helped keep down lamb production in many areas he said 
