a man accused of attacking five women was 
convicted of rape after the victims identified him as their 
assailant by listening to his taperecorded voice 
scott carroll 27 a new york city factory worker was found 
guilty thursday of 31 charges in a 54count indictment including 
four rapes and one attempted rape 
the jury which deliberated for 10 days deadlocked on 21 
charges including one rape an attempted rape and robbery he was 
acquitted on two burglary charges 
carroll displayed no emotion when the verdict was announced 
his attorney eric naiburg conceded during the sixweek trial 
that one man committed all the crimes but contended that police had 
arrested the wrong man he said he would appeal the conviction 
in most of the incidents the assailant wore a mask or it was 
too dark to see his face the victims testified 
according to prosecutor michael ahearn carroll stalked his 
victims for days confronted them in their bedrooms as they slept 
and put a screwdriver to their throats usually the victims were 
blond and attractive ranging in age from 10 to 55 
the attacks at homes on long islands affluent south shore began 
in january 1983 and ended in february 1987 when carroll was 
arrested 
he faces a maximum of 25 years on each rape conviction and 
ahearn said he would request the maximum on each count to run 
consecutively suffolk county judge stuart namm set sentencing for 
june 22 
six victims four of rape and two of attempted rape picked 
carroll from a voice lineup by listening to recordings of his 
