<TEXT>
irans powerful parliament speaker on 
friday repeated his governments claim that tehran is at war with 
the united states and called for an arms buildup to fight the 
americans in the persian gulf 
the americans have officially entered into a war with us 
hashemi rafsanjani told revolutionary guards commanders he was 
quoted by the official islamic republic news agency which was 
monitored in nicosia 
we are really at war with the united states at the present 
time 
six newly arrived us warships took up station in the arabian 
sea and two others sailed into the gulf 
but there was no sign of hostilities as the us frigates 
pharris and elmer montgomery accompanied by the missile frigate 
john h sides passed through the strait of hormuz where iranian 
speedboats have attacked two commercial ships in recent days 
the pharris and elmer montgomery are part of an eightship 
battle group headed by the aircraft carrier forrestal that 
arrived in the arabian sea this week to provide air support for 
us convoy and patrol operations in the gulf 
rafsanjani also told moslem worshipers at a weekly prayer 
session in tehran university that if the united states fought iran 
they must wait to receive lots of their youths dead bodies 
iranian leaders have repeatedly said they consider that their 
country has been at war with the united states since the us navy 
buildup in the gulf in july to protect americanflagged ships from 
iranian attack 
irna quoted rafsanjani as saying should this war extend to 
new frontiers the americans will simply take delivery of the 
bodies of americans throughout the world 
tension heightened since the americans destroyed iranian 
offshore oil platforms and sank an iranian minelayer in the gulf 
last year 
us warships and aircraft sank or disabled six iranian vessels 
in a string of clashes april 18 in the most serious confrontation 
since the us intervention 
iranian anger mounted after a longrange raid by iraqi warplanes 
on the larak island oil terminal in the southern gulf may 14 in 
which five tankers were set ablaze 
iran claimed the americans jammed its radar and radio systems to 
help the iraqis us officials denied that 
rafsanjani reiterated that allegation friday and said us 
ships guided iraqi forces and caused trouble for our defensive 
forces iran reported 
despite the fiery rhetoric the iranians are clearly outgunned 
by the us navy in the gulf especially since two of their 
frigates were either sunk or crippled in last months naval clashes 
those two britishbuilt warships comprised half the major 
operational warships the iranians had 
the iranians still have several missile boats and a fleet of 
armed speedboats manned by revolutionary guards which have 
attacked two neutral merchant ships in the gulf this week after a 
threeweek lull 
following baghdads recapture last month of the faw peninsula in 
southern iraq seized by the iranians in february 1986 ayatollah 
ruhollah khomeini dismissed the armed forces chief of staff brig 
gen ismael sohrabi 
unconfirmed reports from tehran noted that other senior officers 
have been replaced heightening the belief that khomeini seeks a 
more aggressive strategy to make up for the chain of recent defeats 
rafsanjani closely allied with the revolutionary guards corps 
is considered the most powerful figure in iran after khomeini and 
is the revolutionary patriarchs represenative on the supreme 
defense council 
the council determines irans military strategy in the 
7yearold war 
the supreme defense council called april 18 on iranians to fight 
the united states 
a foreign ministry statement on the same day warned the united 
states to expect a severe response from iran alleging that 
american military helicopters fought on the iraqi side in the 
recapture of faw 
