<TEXT>
thousands of paramilitary troops and 
police fanned out across punjab state friday and raided sikh 
hideouts after reports that militant sikhs murdered 43 people in an 
overnight crime spree 
police said a security red alert was issued in punjab where 
sikhs have allegedly murdered 195 people since may 9 when a 
government hold on the sikhs golden temple began 
the siege of the holy shrine ended wednesday with the surrender 
of the last of the militants holed up inside at least 42 people 
mainly sikh militants were killed during the 10day standoff 
reporters were taken to the temple friday for the first time 
since the siege and saw bloodstains bullet marks and arms and 
ammunition 
the temple complex normally visited by 10000 pilgrims a day 
looked shabby and deserted a stench came from canisters used by 
the radicals as toilets during the siege 
the guru granth sahib the holy book of the sikhs lay under a 
cloth on the floor there was a burn mark across the cloth that 
appeared to have been made by a bullet passing close to its surface 
at least 43 people were killed in seven separate attacks in 
punjab late thursday and friday united news of india reported 
five of the victims killed thursday night were hindu migrant 
workers from the eastern indian state of bihar who were lined up 
against a wall and shot uni said 
it was the second attack on migrant workers this week 
suggesting that the extremists were trying to undercut the mainstay 
of punjab states economy which is agriculture 
other victims thursday night included six killed in jalandhar 
district six killed in bhatinda district and three people were 
shot to death in separate incidents around the state 
on friday five people were killed in a bomb attack on a bus 
near the town of pathankot 90 miles north of amritsar police 
imposed a curfew in pathankot after 10 others were killed in 
separate bomb attacks uni said 
eight other deaths occured in gurdaspur district on friday 
we fear sikh terrorists will start a new wave of violence in 
fact they are already on a killing spree the director general of 
punjab police kps gill told reporters in amritsar 
he said police were put on extended hours and were under order 
to arrest and interrogate any suspect uni said police imposed a 
curfew on pathankot 
time has come to hit the terrorists with iron fist and this 
is what we are going to do he said 
at least 9000 police and paramilitary troops raided suspected 
hideouts of sikh radicals in amritsar gurdashpur and jalandhar 
districts a police officer told the associated press he spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
the districts are considered strongholds of sikh militants who 
have been fighting since 1982 for an independent homeland in 
punjab the golden temple sikhisms holiest shrine has become a 
base for guerrillas waging the war 
gill said authorities recovered 44 weapons including 
chinesemade ak47 rifles light machine guns grenades and 4900 
rounds of ammunition from inside the temple friday he said police 
also found 340000 in indian currency 
the latest killings raised to at least 1131 the number of 
people murdered by sikh extremists in punjab this year in all of 
1987 about 1030 people died 
sikhs whose religion was founded 500 years ago as an 
alternative to hinduism and islam claim they are discriminated 
against by hindus sikhs are a minority in india but comprise a 
majority in punjab 
