the nuclear regulatory commission voted 
unanimously friday to approve a fullpower license to commonwealth 
edison co for the second reactor at its braidwood nuclear power 
plant near chicago 
the decision came five months after the commission granted the 
utility a lowpower license for the reactor nrc spokesman frank 
ingram said 
the reactor will be brought up to full power gradually and is 
expected to be fully operational by fall generating 11 kilowatts 
of electricity the company said 
the first of braidwoods two reactors was licensed for 
fullpower operation on july 2 1987 ingram said 
the nrc action brought to 12 the number of fully licensed 
reactors edison operates at six illinois plants and marked the 
completion of a nuclearplant construction program it began in the 
early 1970s the utility said 
