on a platform stage 
an hour later the strains of a chamber music concert sounded at 
the nearby dock street theater the first of dozens of performances 
indoors and out throughout charleston over 17 days 
the festival was founded by composer gian carlo menotti and is 
named after the similar festival he founded in spoleto italy 
fridays opening ceremonies also kicked off four days of events 
celebrating the bicentennial of south carolinas ratification of 
the constitution 
