<TEXT>
a citizens group is calling for a boycott of 
the major news program in mexico accusing it of dedicating 97 
percent of its time the presidential candidate of the governing 
party 
the active and peaceful civic resistance organization 
distributed handbills calling on the public to stop watching 24 
horas the nationally broadcast news program of the private 
televisa network 
it said news of candidate carlos salinas de gortari dominated 
the broadcasts 
the public has a right to choose with its preference or 
rejection of the type of information that it wants to receive 
the handbills say 
let the public make its decision and maintain it until it can 
be proven that these news shows have stopped being instruments of 
one party and have become true outlets of objective information 
the handbills conclude 
no one was immediately available at televisa offices to comment 
on the boycott call 
salinas degortari candidate of the governing institutional 
revolutionary party known as the pri is certain to win the july 6 
elections over five minority party candidates 
rodolfo bermejo who identified himself as civic resistances 
training director said in a phone interview friday that the group 
is an independent nonpartisan organization in 29 mexican cities 
he said it formed in 1986 after controversial elections in the 
northern border state of chihuahua won by the pri and considered a 
major setback to the opposition national action party 
televisa reorganized its news programs in response to numerous 
complaints of biased coverage in the chihuahua elections adding an 
evening news program that it said would emphasize provincial 
coverage and add additional viewpoints 
minority candidates have complained frequently that they are 
prevented from equal access to broadcast media and newspapers but 
president miguel de la madrid and other pri and government leaders 
reject the accusation 
civic resistance did not explain how it arrived at the figure of 
97 percent of 24 horas programming being dedicated to salinas de 
gortari 
a study done by the governments channel 11 found that 24 horas 
in february dedicated 67 bites or 86 percent of its campaign 
coverage to salinas de gortari said raul trejo a researcher at 
the national autonomous university of mexico 
in an interview in this weeks mexico journal magazine trejo 
attributed the heavy coverage to the political ties that exist 
between the heads of this communications enterprise and the pri and 
the insistence by the party that televisa provide coverage of the 
pri candidate 
