<TEXT>
marion g romney president of the mormon 
churchs council of the twelve apostles and a developer of the 
faiths extensive welfare program died friday at age 90 
next in line by tradition to become president of the 65 
millionmember church romney died at his home of causes related to 
his age said church spokesman don lefevre 
the major missions of the church will forever reflect the 
kindliness wisdom gospel scholarship and faith of president 
marion g romney said a joint statement issued by the churchs 
governing first presidency 
romneys funeral was scheduled for noon monday in the tabernacle 
on temple square 
as the most senior member of the twelve romney by tradition 
was the likely successor to the presidency of the church of jesus 
christ of latterday saints had he outlived president ezra taft 
benson the former us agriculture secretary 
however because of failing health romney stopped participating 
actively in church affairs well before benson 88 became church 
president in november 1985 
with romneys death howard w hunter acting president of the 
twelve for more than a year becomes the groups official leader 
and probable successor to benson church presidents serve for life 
among romneys achievements was creation as a salt lake city 
leader of a prototype for the churchs welfare system organized 
in 1936 to combat the impact of the great depression 
the system a network of farms canneries and bakeries that 
provide employment and goods for needy church members is based on 
a philosophy of selfhelp that has drawn praise from president 
reagan recipients are required to work at one of the enterprises 
or perform some other service in return for assistance 
after romney was called to general leadership in the church in 
april 1941 as an assistant to the council of the twelve he was 
named assistant managing director of the church welfare program a 
position he held until 1959 he served as general chairman of the 
welfare committee from 1959 to 1963 
he also was named in october 1951 to the twelve which assists 
the threemember first presidency he became a member of the first 
presidency in 1972 
he was a man of great warmth love kindness and patience 
said utah gov norm bangerter a former mormon stake president 
former gov scott m matheson romneys cousin recalled a 
long and very gratifying association with him he has been a great 
inspiration to me 
romney also was a cousin to george romney the former governor 
of michigan and candidate for the republican nomination for 
president in 1968 
during his career romney supervised missionary efforts of the 
church in mexico europe south africa and asia in 1961 he 
formally organized in mexico city the churchs first 
spanishspeaking stake a geographical unit comprised of several 
congregations 
romney had been a counselor to the late church presidents harold 
b lee and spencer w kimball between 1972 and 1985 when kimball 
died at age 90 on nov 5 1985 benson his successor replaced 
romney on the first presidency and romney became president of the 
twelve by seniority 
romney was born sept 19 1897 in colonia juarez mexico where 
many mormon families had settled after the church dropped its 
doctrinally based practice of polygamy in 1890 
romney and his family were forced out of mexico by 
revolutionaries when he was 14 they eventually settled in idaho 
after serving in the us army in 1918 romney graduated in 1920 
from ricks normal college in rexburg idaho he served three years 
as a missionary in australia before enrolling at the university of 
utah where he earned a bachelors degree in 1926 and later a law 
degree 
romney is survived by two sons and eight grandchildren his 
wife ida jensen romney died march 9 1979 
</TEXT>
