<TEXT>
retired marine col peter julien ortiz one of 
the corps most colorful and highly decorated world war ii 
veterans will be buried at arlington national cemetery on monday 
the pentagon announced friday 
ortiz 75 died may 16 in prescott ariz of cancer he was the 
most decorated marine to serve with the office of strategic 
services the forerunner of the cia 
his exploits during the war were the subject of two different 
motion pictures 13 rue madeleine starring james cagney and 
operation top secret starring cornel wilde 
ortiz born in new york city and educated in france received 
numerous decorations from the french and british governments for 
his exploits in addition to two navy crosses the legion of merit 
and two purple hearts 
he was best known for his work in organizing french resistance 
units and coordinating the delivery of arms ammunition and 
equipment to the underground after being dropped behind the lines 
with a britishorganized oss team in 1943 
ortiz who once assisted four downed raf pilots in escaping 
occupied territory became the subject of an intense search by the 
german gestapo and ultimately turned himself in to the germans in 
1944 to spare local villagers from reprisals he spent the 
remainder of the war as a prisoner 
ortiz will be buried with full military honors at arlington at 1 
pm monday the pentagon said he is survived by his wife the 
former jean morlan and a son marine maj pj ortiz jr 
</TEXT>
