<TEXT>
nova pharmaceutical corp has agreed to a joint 
venture with smithkline beckman corp to develop and market a 
variety of painkilling and central nervous system drugs pending 
approval from both firms boards baltimorebased nova announced 
the preliminary agreement estimated to be worth 725 million 
to nova eventually will give philadelphiabased smithkline an 
estimated 20 percent stake in nova which was founded in 1982 
the two firms would be advancing work on a range of drugs nova 
has developed including a class of painkillers targeted at 
bradykinin which nova and the johns hopkins medical institutions 
report plays a key role in relaying pain messages to the nervous 
system the findings were reported in the current issue of the 
proceedings of the national academy of science 
this is quite significant for nova arda m minocherhomjee 
a healthcare analyst with cable howse amp ragen inc in seattle 
said of the joint venture it gives them access to an excellent 
marketing partner and furthermore it gives them the capital 
needed to develop their products 
after the agreement was announced thursday novas stock closed 
